.TH AUX 7 "June 2026" "A/UX Workstation" "Local Commands"
.SH NAME
aux \- overview of the local software on this A/UX workstation
.SH DESCRIPTION
This machine layers a modern terminal stack over stock A/UX 3.1.1:
ncurses 5.7 (TERMINFO in /.bashrc), the rxvt 2.6.4 port (rxvt(1)),
an X11R6 client library build, ProFont served as SNF, and the tools
below.  The full plain-text manual lives in /DOCUMENT; sources, build
notes, and recovery recipes are in the se30 repository on the
controlling Mac.
.SH COMMANDS
auxtop(1) process monitor; dialc(1) Dialtone AOL client; auxfont(1)
desktop font switcher; auxagent(1) remote exec/file agent with
auxadmin(1); auxfetch(1), auxsaver(1), bgroot(1) desktop furniture;
resizewin(1) X test helper; dialc-x(1) and auxtop-x(1) fvwm
launchers.
.SH CAVEATS
Run sync(1) after writes you care about (crashes revert unsynced
data).  Replace running binaries with mv-then-cp (text file busy).
Keep the bell visual (audible can crash the emulator).  Curses
programs must defeat tty output post-processing; see /DOCUMENT.
.SH SEE ALSO
DOCUMENT in /, the se30 repository
